title: For Sale:  Hawes Western Marshal
postcontent: I have a Hawes Western Marshal (sometimes spelled Marshall, but not spelled that way on the gun) single action .357 magnum in very good condition.  It shoots very well and has an excellent trigger, bright bore and 6" barrel.  These guns have not been made since the early 50's, but this one is in very good shape considering its age.  You can tell that it hasn't been shot much by the light drag mark on the cylinder.  There is some wear on the alloy ejector housing.  I had the trigger guard assembly powder coated since it was also alloy and had lost a lot of its original finish.  I think the powder coating came out very nice.  I did not have the ejector housing powder coated because I bought this gun to carry in a holster and figured the ejector housing would just wear again from holster use.  However, the ejector housing could be powder coated as well if desired.  The only other cosmetic problem is that someone evidently took pliers to the cylinder pin which marred it.  It would not be much trouble to refinish.  It has an adjustable rear sight.  I really like this gun and hate to sell it, but I need the money.  Offers will be considered and I only accept cash, money order or PayPal.  The best way to contact me is to text or call 2o8-35two-2413.  My name is Preston.  Thanks for looking.
